<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sort of......Kyo has his own style and moveset. A swing with each hand that can be followed up with different moves, a motioned grab, a kick that swings up into the air and arcs straight down, a reversal...etc.<br>
<br>
Ryu clones generally have fireball+uppercut move+huricane kick. No more moves than that, and if they do they only give them one more. Supers are generally the same, either a super fireball or a rising dragon punch variation. The lack of originality, that's what i was talking about. I assume the one you are referring to is KOF 99-there are 3 versions of kyo, which coincidently is part of the story. I wouldn't say it was any different from evil ryu or shin gouki (akuma).<br>
<br>
If you look carefully, all 2D fighters actually use different pieces of the body on different characters. I was playing Garou:mark of the wolves and i noticed the 2nd last boss has the same pants as gato. Capcom games generally have at least 3-6 shoto characters that have the exact same sprite, they just add a different head (Akuma, ken, ryu, dan, sean). They are the same sprite, they just make it look slightly different. Ken sort of sways from side to side, Dan does the same animation on the spot. SFEX has at least 7 shoto characters (that's including characters like sakura that have the same moves but not the same animation), i can't remember how many there are in SFA3 and i'm too lazy to fire it up to check.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Anyway, my favorite is Voldo! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
